; lib/seq.nuc — retained as a placeholder after removal of the fixed-type
; IntIndexable, Call, and BinaryCall protocols (C2.5, design/stage11/cleanup2.md).
;
; Those protocols named the `invoke` capability over concrete types (i32, ptr).
; The parametric replacements are (UnaryFn Arg Ret) and (FoldFn Acc Elem) in
; lib/iterator.nuc. The call mechanism itself (a value in head position routes
; to the `invoke` generic) does not depend on protocol conformance — an `invoke`
; method works without it. See docs/builtins.md §invoke and examples/callable.nuc.
